50|$|LCMV causes callitrichid {{hepatitis}} in New World primates. The {{onset of}} the infection is nonspecific and may include fever, anorexia, dyspnea, weakness and lethargy. Jaundice is characteristic and <b>petechial</b> hemorrhages may develop. Prostration and death usually follow.|$|E
